ðŸ’¡ Decision Framework

Ask these questions:

1. Is ACID compliance required? â†’ MySQL
2. Will the data structure change frequently? â†’ NoSQL
3. Need complex joins and relationships? â†’ MySQL
4. Expecting massive scale? â†’ NoSQL
5. Require strong consistency? â†’ MySQL
6. Building real-time analytics? â†’ NoSQL

ðŸŒŸ Hybrid Approach

Many modern applications use both:

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Web Application] --> B[MySQL: User accounts]
    A --> C[MySQL: Transactions]
    A --> D[Redis: Session storage]
    A --> E[MongoDB: User content]
    A --> F[Elasticsearch: Search]
```

Example hybrid usage:

Â· MySQL for user data and transactions
Â· Redis for caching and sessions
Â· MongoDB for user-generated content
Â· Elasticsearch for search functionality

