ðŸš€ When to Choose Which

Choose MySQL if:

Â· You need transactions and data integrity
Â· Your data is highly structured
Â· You require complex reporting
Â· Your team knows SQL well

Choose NoSQL if:

Â· You need to scale horizontally
Â· Your schema is evolving
Â· You're handling large volumes of data
Â· You need high write performance

Both have their place in modern application development, and many successful companies use a combination of both technologies to leverage their respective strengths.
